  "texts": [
    "Importantly, participants did not know the identity of their partner, and based on results from Study 4 assumed they were human.",
    "In the human partner condition, participants received the scenario sent by their human counterpart.",
    "In the AI case, participants received one of the vignettes that were presented in Study 1.",
    "After reading the scenario and rating it in terms of negativity positivity and distinct emotions (similar to Study 1), participants were asked to provide a reappraisal to the scenario and also received the reappraisal provided by their counterpart.",
    "Notice that when analyzing the results of this study we only focused on comparing human and GPT-4 reappraisals to the human scenarios."
  ],
